<section>
  <h2>What FISCO does</h2>
  <p>FISCO is a template for IFIs to operationalise the EU’s reformed economic governance framework. It assesses both the medium-term fiscal-structural plan's compliance with Regulation (EU) 2024/1263 and its annual implementation against the agreed net expenditure path commitment and other debt, deficit and control account criteria.</p>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Medium-Term Plan assessment</h3>
      <p>Tests the proposed net expenditure path against debt sustainability, deficit, and minimum-effort safeguards.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Implementation monitoring</h3>
      <p>Tracks annual and cumulative deviations from net expenditure plans in the control account, and flags any breaches of the 0.3% and 0.6% of GDP thresholds.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Built for IFIs</h3>
      <p>Transparent formulas, automatic data updates from Eurostat and AMECO, and a step-by-step workflow with video tutorials.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
